00:59:51.280 --> 00:59:52.670
to be the head and not the tail, above

00:59:52.680 --> 00:59:54.590
and not beneath. And that's why I think

00:59:54.600 --> 00:59:56.430
prayer that is effective is a winning

00:59:56.440 --> 00:59:57.470
prayer.

00:59:57.480 --> 00:59:59.190
It's not a whining prayer. You're a

00:59:59.200 --> 01:00:02.270
believing believer.

01:00:02.280 --> 01:00:04.230
God is able to do through

01:00:04.240 --> 01:00:06.310
you exceedingly, abundantly, above all

01:00:06.320 --> 01:00:08.310
that you dare ask or think,

01:00:08.320 --> 01:00:11.230
according to the power that works in

01:00:11.240 --> 01:00:14.430
you. And you're a believing believer.

01:00:14.440 --> 01:00:16.190
I'm not a doubter.

01:00:16.200 --> 01:00:19.270
I'm a believer, and I'm an overcomer by

01:00:19.280 --> 01:00:22.030
the blood of the Lamb and by the word of

01:00:22.040 --> 01:00:24.070
my testimony. You either believe it or

01:00:24.080 --> 01:00:26.790
you don't.

01:00:26.800 --> 01:00:29.190
I'm not a victim.

01:00:29.200 --> 01:00:30.630
I'm a victor. That's

01:00:30.630 --> 01:00:30.640
what

01:00:30.640 --> 01:00:31.430
the Lord told me. He said,

01:00:31.440 --> 01:00:33.150
'Braden,

01:00:33.160 --> 01:00:35.110
you can't be a victim and go

01:00:35.120 --> 01:00:37.150
on the glory side and the

01:00:37.160 --> 01:00:39.910
victory side. A victim

01:00:39.910 --> 01:00:39.920
doesn't

01:00:39.920 --> 01:00:42.230
walk on the victory

01:00:42.230 --> 01:00:42.240
side.''Well,

01:00:42.240 --> 01:00:44.350
I've had all this.'The Lord said,

01:00:44.360 --> 01:00:48.150
'Brandon, who hasn't

01:00:48.150 --> 01:00:48.160
had

01:00:48.160 --> 01:00:50.710
a story?

01:00:50.720 --> 01:00:52.350
Everybody has a story. Everybody's had

01:00:52.360 --> 01:00:53.590
something hard they've been through in

01:00:53.600 --> 01:00:55.750
their life. You're not

01:00:55.760 --> 01:00:57.870
anything different. Yeah, you have a

01:00:57.880 --> 01:00:59.590
child that's overcome special needs, and

01:00:59.590 --> 01:00:59.600
you've

01:00:59.600 --> 01:01:01.710
got a child that's overcoming autism,

01:01:01.720 --> 01:01:03.190
and you've got this stuff going on, but

01:01:03.200 --> 01:01:04.990
there's somebody else with a worse story

01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:07.750
than you.

01:01:07.760 --> 01:01:10.670
And you can either camp around your sad

01:01:10.680 --> 01:01:12.030
pity party

01:01:12.040 --> 01:01:13.950
and how you feel sorry for yourself,

01:01:13.960 --> 01:01:15.670
but you can look across

01:01:15.680 --> 01:01:17.150
the street and see somebody that

01:01:17.160 --> 01:01:19.110
has it a lot worse.

01:01:19.120 --> 01:01:20.230
And there's always somebody that's

01:01:20.240 --> 01:01:21.750
overcoming something different than you

01:01:21.760 --> 01:01:25.070
are.'But

01:01:25.080 --> 01:01:28.230
I refuse to be a victim and

01:01:28.240 --> 01:01:30.590
not a victor. The ones that get the

01:01:30.600 --> 01:01:32.310
job done are the ones that have

01:01:32.310 --> 01:01:32.320
that

01:01:32.320 --> 01:01:34.430
bulldog faith and

01:01:34.430 --> 01:01:34.440
say,

01:01:34.440 --> 01:01:37.710
'I

01:01:37.710 --> 01:01:37.720
refuse.'As

01:01:37.720 --> 01:01:39.430
the Lord was driving around today,

01:01:39.440 --> 01:01:41.150
He said, 'You've got to practice like a

01:01:41.160 --> 01:01:43.310
champion.

01:01:43.320 --> 01:01:46.110
You've got to

01:01:46.110 --> 01:01:46.120
believe.'What

01:01:46.120 --> 01:01:50.590
did Michael Jordan do,

01:01:50.600 --> 01:01:53.510
in his natural ability, to practice to

01:01:53.520 --> 01:01:55.030
be a winner?

01:01:55.040 --> 01:01:56.990
You've got to think this is the major

01:01:57.000 --> 01:01:59.230
leagues. That's what He said to me.

01:01:59.240 --> 01:02:00.870
'You've got to think this is the major

01:02:00.880 --> 01:02:02.670
leagues. You can't think in the minor

01:02:02.680 --> 01:02:04.190
leagues. This isn't college level

01:02:04.200 --> 01:02:05.990
anymore.

01:02:07.920 --> 01:02:09.630
You've got to think and train like a

01:02:09.630 --> 01:02:09.640
champion.'That's

01:02:09.640 --> 01:02:10.990
what Pastor Chip

01:02:10.990 --> 01:02:11.000
would

01:02:11.000 --> 01:02:12.350
even tell us.

01:02:12.360 --> 01:02:14.150
You've got to think and train like a

01:02:14.160 --> 01:02:16.390
champion. You can't be thinking the

01:02:16.400 --> 01:02:18.390
way you're thinking anymore,

01:02:18.400 --> 01:02:21.230
worried about whatever.

01:02:21.240 --> 01:02:22.790
What did Michael Jordan do to get where he

01:02:22.790 --> 01:02:22.800
is?

01:02:22.800 --> 01:02:24.390
What did Derek Jeter do? What

01:02:24.400 --> 01:02:26.230
did John Elway do?

01:02:26.240 --> 01:02:28.030
What did

01:02:28.040 --> 01:02:30.110
Troy Aikman, Michael Irvin, or Emmitt

01:02:30.120 --> 01:02:33.270
Smith, the greats, do to get where they

01:02:33.280 --> 01:02:34.270
were?

01:02:34.280 --> 01:02:35.790
Did they sit and feel sorry for

01:02:35.800 --> 01:02:37.750
themselves? No, they acted, and they had

01:02:37.760 --> 01:02:41.470
a swag that was successful.

01:02:41.480 --> 01:02:43.470
After they got to the NFL, after they

01:02:43.480 --> 01:02:45.710
got to these places, they didn't still

01:02:45.720 --> 01:02:48.950
act like they did in college.

01:02:48.960 --> 01:02:50.590
They didn't act like they did in high

01:02:50.600 --> 01:02:54.070
school. You go from glory to glory. And

01:02:54.080 --> 01:02:55.550
the only way I can tell you all this,

01:02:55.560 --> 01:02:56.870
maybe, is to bring it to

01:02:56.870 --> 01:02:56.880
a

01:02:56.880 --> 01:02:59.510
natural level for you: sports.

01:02:59.520 --> 01:03:02.350
I love sports. But you go from glory to

01:03:02.360 --> 01:03:06.990
glory to glory to glory.

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:10.190
And the way you are in the pros is not the

01:03:10.200 --> 01:03:11.710
way you're going to act when you were in

01:03:11.720 --> 01:03:13.270
high school.

01:03:13.280 --> 01:03:15.550
You've got to carry yourself differently.

01:03:15.550 --> 01:03:15.560
You're

01:03:15.560 --> 01:03:17.830
a victor.

01:03:19.320 --> 01:03:21.630
You're a champion. You've got

01:03:21.640 --> 01:03:23.110
to train like a

01:03:23.120 --> 01:03:25.590
champion. You've got to act like it. And

01:03:25.600 --> 01:03:27.070
I'm just trying to help stir you

01:03:27.080 --> 01:03:29.390
up so you don't have that victim

01:03:29.400 --> 01:03:31.750
mentality. Because if you have a victim

01:03:31.760 --> 01:03:32.950
mentality, you're never going to have a

01:03:32.960 --> 01:03:35.070
winner's mentality,

01:03:35.080 --> 01:03:36.950
and you're never going to be able to

01:03:36.960 --> 01:03:39.230
take over things and say, 'Listen, I've

01:03:39.240 --> 01:03:41.310
got the ring.'You know, like

01:03:41.320 --> 01:03:43.110
Pastor Chip; he has

01:03:43.110 --> 01:03:43.120
that

01:03:43.120 --> 01:03:45.230
old championship ring on his finger

01:03:45.240 --> 01:03:47.510
that he got from the Astros when he

01:03:47.520 --> 01:03:49.870
was a scout.

01:03:49.880 --> 01:03:52.070
It's a different mentality.

01:03:52.080 --> 01:03:53.870
So, I want to stretch you to believe

01:03:53.880 --> 01:03:56.630
bigger,

01:03:56.640 --> 01:04:01.790
to stretch yourself to think bigger.

01:04:01.800 --> 01:04:03.670
You've got to think bigger in these last

01:04:03.680 --> 01:04:04.950
days

01:04:04.960 --> 01:04:07.150
and not have that victim

01:04:07.160 --> 01:04:08.990
mentality. The Lord corrects me all

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:10.150
the time because sometimes I feel sorry for

01:04:10.160 --> 01:04:11.630
myself.

01:04:11.630 --> 01:04:11.640
No,

01:04:11.640 --> 01:04:13.349
stop that!

01:04:13.359 --> 01:04:17.150
I've created you for more than that.

01:04:17.160 --> 01:04:19.950
Go back to the fundamentals.

01:04:19.960 --> 01:04:22.470
Go back to the basics of Christianity.

01:04:22.480 --> 01:04:24.110
Go back to when you're having a hard day.

01:04:24.120 --> 01:04:25.270
'How did you get here in the

01:04:25.280 --> 01:04:26.910
first place, Brandon?'Spending time with

01:04:26.920 --> 01:04:28.590
Me. That was all about the

01:04:28.600 --> 01:04:30.790
friendship sermon that I told you last

01:04:30.800 --> 01:04:32.990
time.

01:04:33.000 --> 01:04:35.430
Go back to the basics.

01:04:35.440 --> 01:04:38.590
Don't forget the fundamentals:

01:04:38.600 --> 01:04:40.630
reading your Bible, praying in

01:04:40.640 --> 01:04:42.710
the spirit, and fellowship with Me,

01:04:42.720 --> 01:04:46.190
singing songs. Go back to the ABCs.

01:04:46.200 --> 01:04:48.070
When you're a goose in the fog, it's

01:04:48.080 --> 01:04:50.870
like training in war. They

01:04:50.880 --> 01:04:52.910
repeat it

01:04:52.920 --> 01:04:55.150
until

01:04:55.160 --> 01:04:57.030
it's in that muscle memory. They just

01:04:57.040 --> 01:04:58.349
act.

01:04:58.359 --> 01:05:00.270
The moment something happens in war,

01:05:00.280 --> 01:05:02.670
they don't

01:05:02.680 --> 01:05:04.790
freeze because it's so grounded in them;

01:05:04.790 --> 01:05:04.800
it's

01:05:04.800 --> 01:05:06.590
just their muscle memory.

01:05:06.600 --> 01:05:08.430
Remember that doctor at the

01:05:08.430 --> 01:05:08.440
prayer

01:05:08.440 --> 01:05:10.510
conference? He said most

01:05:10.520 --> 01:05:12.270
wrecks always happen within a couple

01:05:12.280 --> 01:05:14.750
miles of the house

01:05:14.760 --> 01:05:16.390
because you're on autopilot. You don't

01:05:16.400 --> 01:05:17.710
think; you can just go there

01:05:17.720 --> 01:05:19.310
without even thinking.

01:05:19.320 --> 01:05:20.430
You don't even realize what street

01:05:20.440 --> 01:05:21.590
you're turning down a lot of times

01:05:21.590 --> 01:05:21.600
because

01:05:21.600 --> 01:05:23.150
you can be thinking about something else.

01:05:23.150 --> 01:05:23.160
And

01:05:23.160 --> 01:05:25.270
because you have

01:05:25.280 --> 01:05:26.790
muscle memory—you've done it so many

01:05:26.790 --> 01:05:26.800
times—your

01:05:26.800 --> 01:05:28.349
mind doesn't even have to

01:05:28.359 --> 01:05:30.390
really process within a couple miles of

01:05:30.400 --> 01:05:31.470
your house. You can just go there with

01:05:31.480 --> 01:05:33.390
your eyes closed, basically,

01:05:33.400 --> 01:05:35.390
because your mind already knows which

01:05:35.400 --> 01:05:36.910
way it's going to go before you even do

01:05:36.920 --> 01:05:38.550
it, because it's muscle memory. Just like that.

01:05:38.550 --> 01:05:38.560
That is

01:05:38.560 --> 01:05:41.070
grounded in you,

01:05:41.080 --> 01:05:42.310
and that's why we have to be with the

01:05:42.320 --> 01:05:44.430
word. It's just in us; you react

01:05:44.440 --> 01:05:46.110
immediately. What did you

01:05:46.110 --> 01:05:46.120
say

01:05:46.120 --> 01:05:47.910
about first response? What

01:05:47.920 --> 01:05:50.470
was your first response

01:05:50.470 --> 01:05:50.480
whenever

01:05:50.480 --> 01:05:51.710
he hurt his finger? When you do

01:05:51.720 --> 01:05:53.270
these things, what's your first

01:05:53.280 --> 01:05:55.590
response?

01:05:55.600 --> 01:05:57.710
The moment you come into

01:05:57.720 --> 01:06:02.390
trouble, what's your first response?

01:06:02.400 --> 01:06:04.030
Regardless of what you're going through,

01:06:04.040 --> 01:06:06.150
your first response matters.

01:06:06.160 --> 01:06:08.590
Your first response matters.

01:06:08.600 --> 01:06:11.070
It's not dropping a bad word

01:06:11.080 --> 01:06:13.550
or yelling at your kids, your wife,

01:06:13.560 --> 01:06:17.550
or your dog. What's your first response?

01:06:17.560 --> 01:06:18.750
The word.

01:06:18.760 --> 01:06:21.830
It's in you. It's muscle memory. What

01:06:21.840 --> 01:06:24.310
comes out of you out of the abundance of

01:06:24.320 --> 01:06:28.750
your heart? The mouth speaks. What's

01:06:28.760 --> 01:06:31.870
in

01:06:31.880 --> 01:06:34.270
abundance in your heart?

01:06:34.280 --> 01:06:36.590
Out of the abundance of your heart, the

01:06:36.600 --> 01:06:39.150
mouth speaks. What's your first

01:06:39.160 --> 01:06:42.710
response?

01:06:42.720 --> 01:06:44.070
If it's

01:06:44.080 --> 01:06:45.670
blankety-blank,

01:06:45.680 --> 01:06:47.430
if it's this or that, then you don't

01:06:47.440 --> 01:06:49.291
have enough muscle memory.

01:06:49.880 --> 01:06:51.670
You know, the word needs to become more

01:06:51.670 --> 01:06:51.680
of a

01:06:51.680 --> 01:06:53.790
priority in your life because

01:06:53.790 --> 01:06:53.800
of

01:06:53.800 --> 01:06:55.270
the abundance of your heart. What's in

01:06:55.280 --> 01:06:58.349
the overflow?

01:06:58.359 --> 01:07:00.630
And I challenge myself;

01:07:00.640 --> 01:07:02.110
I'm speaking to myself. It's

01:07:02.120 --> 01:07:02.990
not

01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:05.110
you. Brandon messes up.

01:07:05.120 --> 01:07:06.590
I dropped something on my toe the other

01:07:06.600 --> 01:07:07.990
day with the air conditioner guy there, and I'm

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:09.750
sure he heard me because I said a bad word.

01:07:09.760 --> 01:07:11.550
I'm just being real with you.

01:07:11.560 --> 01:07:14.110
And my son looked at me and he goes—I

01:07:14.110 --> 01:07:14.120
went,

01:07:14.120 --> 01:07:16.830
'Well, there is overflow

01:07:16.840 --> 01:07:19.470
crud. Something I've got to work on. The

01:07:19.480 --> 01:07:21.470
old man came out of that coffin too

01:07:21.480 --> 01:07:23.550
quick.'I'm

01:07:23.560 --> 01:07:26.750
not proud of it, just being real.

01:07:26.760 --> 01:07:28.070
And it's embarrassing. You go,

01:07:28.080 --> 01:07:30.070
'Well, that was embarrassing.

01:07:30.080 --> 01:07:32.110
You haven't been in the word enough.

01:07:32.110 --> 01:07:32.120
The

01:07:32.120 --> 01:07:33.630
first reaction shouldn't have been

01:07:33.640 --> 01:07:35.750
that after you dropped that thing on

01:07:35.760 --> 01:07:38.310
your toe,'and I did. It hurt. So,

01:07:38.320 --> 01:07:39.950
it's just being real. But

01:07:39.960 --> 01:07:42.990
we're all

01:07:42.990 --> 01:07:43.000
a

01:07:43.000 --> 01:07:45.110
work in progress, and I just

01:07:45.120 --> 01:07:46.510
tell you that because you need to hear

01:07:46.520 --> 01:07:47.950
it.

01:07:47.960 --> 01:07:50.190
It's good.

01:07:50.200 --> 01:07:52.270
People need to hear it. But I'm

01:07:52.280 --> 01:07:54.030
going to go from glory to glory. So I

01:07:54.040 --> 01:07:56.310
don't want to bore

01:07:56.310 --> 01:07:56.320
y'all.

01:07:56.320 --> 01:07:57.870
I know you say, 'Oh, Brandon, I thought

01:07:57.880 --> 01:07:59.870
we were here to

01:07:59.870 --> 01:07:59.880
pray.'Well,

01:07:59.880 --> 01:08:01.790
we are. But I try to tell you all

01:08:01.800 --> 01:08:03.910
this because

01:08:03.920 --> 01:08:04.790
that's what I've been dealing with

01:08:04.800 --> 01:08:05.950
today.

01:08:05.960 --> 01:08:07.910
I told Diana, I said we average—if I do an average

01:08:07.910 --> 01:08:07.920
of

01:08:07.920 --> 01:08:10.630
two hours of video a

01:08:10.640 --> 01:08:12.430
day, if I do these live streams five

01:08:12.440 --> 01:08:14.830
times a

01:08:14.830 --> 01:08:14.840
week—I

01:08:14.840 --> 01:08:16.670
told her, I said, 'I do an average of

01:08:16.670 --> 01:08:16.680
50-some

01:08:16.680 --> 01:08:19.430
hours a month of prayer videos with

01:08:19.430 --> 01:08:19.440
y'all.'50-some

01:08:19.440 --> 01:08:21.190
hours of videos because we

01:08:21.200 --> 01:08:23.470
were doing the math on it. And I said

01:08:23.480 --> 01:08:25.110
that's why a lot of you think you know

01:08:25.120 --> 01:08:26.950
me so well.

01:08:26.960 --> 01:08:28.550
I don't know you at all. When you

01:08:28.560 --> 01:08:30.470
come in public, I go—I met a guy

01:08:30.480 --> 01:08:32.070
yesterday; he goes, 'Oh, I watch you. I

01:08:32.080 --> 01:08:34.510
know you so well,'and I'm like,

01:08:34.520 --> 01:08:35.670
'I don't know you at all.'And it's

01:08:35.680 --> 01:08:37.550
awkward for me, so I'm like, 'Okay,

01:08:37.560 --> 01:08:39.670
well, praise God. I don't know you,

01:08:39.680 --> 01:08:40.990
but you think you know

01:08:40.990 --> 01:08:41.000
me.'Okay.

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:42.670
But after you talk to

01:08:42.670 --> 01:08:42.680
somebody—I

01:08:42.680 --> 01:08:46.110
said if I spent 50 hours

01:08:46.120 --> 01:08:48.510
a month talking to Billy Burke,

01:08:48.520 --> 01:08:50.550
I'd know him really

01:08:50.560 --> 01:08:51.910
well.

01:08:51.920 --> 01:08:53.190
And I'm just sitting here talking to a

01:08:53.200 --> 01:08:54.470
camera.

01:08:54.480 --> 01:08:57.030
But you see, I'm transparent.

01:08:57.040 --> 01:08:58.349
I don't try to hype everything

01:08:58.359 --> 01:08:59.789
up. I don't try to be something

01:08:59.799 --> 01:09:01.550
spiritually that I'm not.

01:09:01.560 --> 01:09:03.709
Y'all, I just try to go, 'Hey,

01:09:03.709 --> 01:09:03.719
we're

01:09:03.719 --> 01:09:04.990
all going to get through this and

01:09:05.000 --> 01:09:06.829
we're going to make it

01:09:06.829 --> 01:09:06.839
together.'I

01:09:06.839 --> 01:09:08.190
may be the leader right now in what

01:09:08.200 --> 01:09:09.829
God's called me to do, but I just tell

01:09:09.839 --> 01:09:11.190
you all, 'Hey,

01:09:11.200 --> 01:09:14.470
we all got issues and we all got stuff

01:09:14.480 --> 01:09:16.030
we're working through

01:09:16.040 --> 01:09:18.110
and we're all a work in progress.'And I

01:09:18.120 --> 01:09:20.030
don't care who you are.

01:09:20.040 --> 01:09:21.990
You put your clothes on the

01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:23.749
same way. You all take a poo. You all

01:09:23.759 --> 01:09:25.590
stink. You have to take

01:09:25.600 --> 01:09:27.190
a bath every single day. If you don't,

01:09:27.200 --> 01:09:29.190
you start smelling like B.O. It's just

01:09:29.200 --> 01:09:31.670
part of life.

